Description: Fragment of lip and neck of East Greek pottery transport amphora. Brown-fired glaze on top and outside of lip. Circular stamps on neck. Clay fine buff-brown.
Curator's comments: Probably from Naukratis on grounds of date and fabric; it may have been trimmed. Plausibly from same jar as 2011,5003.498.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0066)
